modules.description: Provides functions for measuring and manipulating time intervals, including duration arithmetic and timestamp comparisons. Works with custom data types for time values and intervals, tailored for Unix-based systems. Used to track elapsed time in network operations and schedule periodic tasks.

Provides sleep operations with nanosecond precision, allowing threads to pause execution for specified durations. Works with 64-bit integer values representing nanoseconds. Used to introduce controlled delays in event-driven network applications.
